<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[142,759,887,1338]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[142,205,887,908]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Male.</emphasis>
Rather large, slender and elegant species. All bristles and pubescence on body (including postoculars an prothoracic bristle) yellowish white, bristles and pubescence of legs reddish yellow. 
<emphasis box="[624,693,979,1000]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Head.</emphasis>
Face whitish yellow, very narrow (0.5¥ as wide as ocellus) but eyes not touching. Frons dark brown. Occiput strongly convex, dark brown, shining. Palp very large (almost 3/5 of eye), elongate ovoid, pale reddish yellow. Proboscis pale, large, as long as eye. Antenna entirely pale yellow with extreme apex and arista dark; first flagellomere elongate triangular, 1.9¥ as long as deep and 1.1¥ as long as scape and pedicel combined. Arista as long as first three joints of antenna, inserted apically on outer face, entirely dark, with short pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[220,318,1316,1338]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[155,233,1860,1879]" captionTargetBox="[255,1333,199,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-47@21.[239,1349,198,1827]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Achalcus tibialis sp. nov. (male). A, wing; B, antenna; C, coxa and femur I; D, femur and tibia II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432017/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Fig. 10B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[142,758,1362,1507]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[142,223,1362,1383]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Thorax</emphasis>
entirely yellowish white with thin dark line on anterior part between ac, extending till 2nd dc. Postnotum with very small blackish frontolateral triangle. six ac, 2¥ as long as distance between rows. Sutural bristle absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[142,758,1531,1829]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[142,248,1531,1552]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Abdomen</emphasis>
with 1st abdominal tergite yellowish white, 2nd dark brown with large white lateral spots, 3rd till 5th black; 2nd sternite white, sternites brownish black from 3rd onwards; 5th sternite with caudal invagination. Genital capsule blackish brown. 
<emphasis box="[606,750,1654,1675]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Hypopygium</emphasis>
. Aedeagus dark, with slight subapical dorsal bend; ventral bristle of surstylus with small apical flag; VEP and DEP evident; postgonites pale, distinctly bifurcate; cercus very long and tapering, with midventral enlargement, baring long curved bristles (
<figureCitation box="[627,706,1807,1829]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="22.[142,220,1121,1140]" captionTargetBox="[142,1422,200,1088]" captionTargetId="figure-368@22.[142,1422,200,1088]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 11. Achalcus tibialis sp. nov. (male). Hypopygium with cercus separated." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432019" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432019/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[142,758,1853,1907]" lastBlockId="20.[806,1422,196,279]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[142,207,1853,1874]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Wing.</emphasis>
Halter pale, squamal fringe yellowish white. Wing pale, with yellow veins, with R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[610,635,1893,1907]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[733,758,1893,1907]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">1+2</subScript>
slightly diverging apically. Proximal section of vein CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[857,865,236,250]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">1</subScript>
2.4¥ as long as apical section; 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1245,1304,227,250]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">CuAx</subScript>
ratio 1.3. Wing length 
<quantity box="[955,1041,257,279]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="20" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1057,1156,257,279]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[155,233,1860,1879]" captionTargetBox="[255,1333,199,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-47@21.[239,1349,198,1827]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Achalcus tibialis sp. nov. (male). A, wing; B, antenna; C, coxa and femur I; D, femur and tibia II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432017/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[806,1422,303,1091]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[806,858,304,325]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Legs</emphasis>
yellowish white including coxae and tarsi. Femur I with erect ventral bristle at basal 1/6, 1.6¥ as long as femur is deep, with one row of rather strong (0.5 ¥ femur depth) inclined av bristles (also basad of basoventral bristle) and four erect very strong pv preapical bristles (
<figureCitation box="[1019,1117,457,479]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[155,233,1860,1879]" captionTargetBox="[255,1333,199,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-47@21.[239,1349,198,1827]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Achalcus tibialis sp. nov. (male). A, wing; B, antenna; C, coxa and femur I; D, femur and tibia II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432017/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
). Femur II with one row of enlarged inclined av bristles, and one row of erect strong pv bristles; three pv bristles in basal 1/4 as long as femur is deep, more apical bristles inclined until middle of femur; seven pv bristles in apical half 1.5¥ as long as femur is deep; femur II with one strong ad, two strong av and one strong pv preapical bristles (
<figureCitation box="[814,912,671,693]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[155,233,1860,1879]" captionTargetBox="[255,1333,199,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-47@21.[239,1349,198,1827]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Achalcus tibialis sp. nov. (male). A, wing; B, antenna; C, coxa and femur I; D, femur and tibia II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432017/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Femur III with one strong ad and one very strong av preapical bristles. Tibia I with one moderately strong dorsal bristle at basal 1/4; tibia II with two strong (&gt; 3 ¥ tibial depth) ad and one strong pd bristles, basal bristles forming ad-pd couple at about basal 1/4; with ten very strong (3 ¥ tibial depth) erect ventral bristles, apical bristles clustered (
<figureCitation box="[1310,1410,855,877]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="21.[155,233,1860,1879]" captionTargetBox="[255,1333,199,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-47@21.[239,1349,198,1827]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 10. Achalcus tibialis sp. nov. (male). A, wing; B, antenna; C, coxa and femur I; D, femur and tibia II." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5432017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5432017/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Fig. 10D</figureCitation>
). Tibia III with three very strong ad and three very strong pd bristles; with long pd pubescence in basal half and 4–5 minute ventral setae amid dense pubescence. Tarsus I pale yellow, slightly darker than tibia; tarsus III with large incision at comb. First tarsomere of leg III 0.7¥ as long as 2nd tarsomere. Body length 
<quantity box="[806,894,1070,1091]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="20" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[806,1021,1116,1138]" box="[806,1021,1116,1138]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[806,922,1116,1138]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Female. U</emphasis>
nknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[806,1422,1162,1215]" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[806,931,1162,1183]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</emphasis>
Refers to the peculiar ventral chaetotaxy of tibia II in this species.
</paragraph>
